<LegalLayout locale="en" title="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="2026-05-08">

  <p>
    The English version is provided for convenience. The legally binding version is the
    French <a href="/fr/confidentialite/">Politique de confidentialité</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    Rugby Olympique Club de Chantilly (R.O.C.C.), a non-profit association under French
    law (loi 1901), is committed to protecting the privacy of its members, partners, and
    visitors. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect personal
    data, in compliance with the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR — EU
    Regulation 2016/679) and the French Data Protection Act of 6 January 1978 as amended.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Rugby Olympique Club de Chantilly</strong><br />
    Non-profit association (loi 1901)<br />
    <span class="placeholder">[Registered office address]</span><br />
    Email: <span class="placeholder">[contact@…]</span>
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Identity data:</strong> first name, last name, date of birth (for membership and Rugby School registration).</li>
    <li><strong>Contact data:</strong> postal address, email, phone.</li>
    <li><strong>Sports-related data:</strong> license, medical certificate, age category.</li>
    <li><strong>Partner data:</strong> company name, contact, partnership project (contact form).</li>
    <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> anonymized IP address, browser type, pages visited (internal audience measurement only, no third-party cookies).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Purposes of Processing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Membership and Rugby School registration management.</li>
    <li>License delivery via the French Rugby Federation (FFR).</li>
    <li>Club-life communications (newsletters, events, matches).</li>
    <li>Partnership and sponsor relationship management.</li>
    <li>Responding to contact form requests.</li>
    <li>Compliance with legal and regulatory obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Legal Basis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Performance of a contract</strong> (membership, partnership).</li>
    <li><strong>Consent</strong> (newsletter, optional communications).</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> of the club (administrative management).</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> (FFR reporting, association records).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Recipients</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Authorized R.O.C.C. board members and volunteers.</li>
    <li>French Rugby Federation (FFR) and departmental committee for license issuance.</li>
    <li>Technical providers (Vercel hosting, GitHub) under GDPR-compliant contracts.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>R.O.C.C. does not sell, rent, or transfer any data to third parties for commercial purposes.</p>

  <h2>6. Retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Member data:</strong> kept during membership, archived 3 years afterward.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact form data:</strong> 12 months max after last interaction.</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymized technical data:</strong> 13 months max (CNIL recommendation).</li>
    <li><strong>Accounting/tax data:</strong> 10 years (legal obligation).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Under the GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Right of access</li>
    <li>Right to rectification</li>
    <li>Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")</li>
    <li>Right to restriction of processing</li>
    <li>Right to data portability</li>
    <li>Right to object</li>
    <li>Right to withdraw consent at any time</li>
    <li>Right to define directives regarding your data after death</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise these rights: <span class="placeholder">[contact@…]</span></p>
  <p>
    You may also lodge a complaint with the French data protection authority (CNIL):
    <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/en/plaintes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cnil.fr/en/plaintes</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Security</h2>
  <p>
    R.O.C.C. implements appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your
    data. Communications with the site are encrypted via HTTPS (TLS).
  </p>

  <h2>9. Cookies and Trackers</h2>
  <p>
    This site uses <strong>no advertising or profiling cookies</strong>. The only items
    potentially set are:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strictly necessary technical cookies (Vercel load balancing).</li>
    <li>Google Fonts (may transmit your IP to Google — see <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a>).</li>
    <li>TikTok embeds may set third-party cookies when a video is played (see <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok Privacy Policy</a>).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>10. Minors</h2>
  <p>
    Rugby School registration involves minors. All personal data relating to minors is
    collected with the explicit consent of the parents/legal guardians and used only
    within the context of supervised sports practice.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    This policy may be updated at any time. The last update date is shown at the top.
    Please review periodically.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>For any data protection question: <span class="placeholder">[contact@…]</span></p>

</LegalLayout>
